title: Elastic Scattering of 24.7 MeV Alpha Particles

x4freetext: Elastic Scattering of 24.7 MeV Alpha Particles

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Physics Letters, Vol.11, Issue.1, p.74 (1964)

x4codes.hlp: Niewodniczanski Institute of Nuclear Physics, Krakow, Poland

x4freetext: The experiment was carried out using
the 120 cm cyclotron of the Institute of Nuclear
Physics, Cracow.
The targets were prepared from spectroscopically or
chemically pure samples by means of vaccum
evaporation or rolling. The thickness of targets in
no case exceeded 2.3 mg/cm2.
Angular distributions were measured using a
semiconductor counter as a detector of alpha
particles. The intensity of the beam was monitored
by two semiconductor detectors, one viewing the
target at a fixed angle of about 30.degr., the second
one counting alpha particles scattered from a gold
target placed in the beam in front of the Faraday cup.
In order to obtain better accuracy in the
determination of the absolute values of the cross
sections several independent measurements were made
with a few different targets for each nuclide.
The error in the angle setting was estimated
to be +-0.1 degr.
* the energy resolution +- 120 keV.
* The errors of the absolute values of the cross
sections were estimated to vary from 2% up to 10%.
